4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would exclude the use or purchase of
6 natural gas or liquefied petroleum gas by certain
7 contractors for use or consumption in the construction
8 of a public highway, road, or bridge from the utility
9 gross receipts tax and utility service use tax.
10 This bill would also exempt certain contractors
11 working on a project for the construction of a public
12 highway, road, or bridge from payment of state sales
13 and use taxes on natural gas and liquefied petroleum
14 gas.
15 This bill would also allow counties and
16 municipalities to adopt complimentary local sales and
17 use tax exemptions.
18
19
20 A BILL
21 TO BE ENTITLED
22 AN ACT
23
24 Relating to taxation; to amend Sections 40-21-83 and
25 40-21-103, Code of Alabama 1975, to exclude the purchase or
26 use of natural gas or liquefied petroleum gas by certain
27 contractors for public highway, road, or bridge construction
28 projects from utility gross receipts and utility service use
