29 taxes; to exempt the purchase of natural gas and liquefied
30 petroleum gas made by certain contractors on public highway,
31 road, or bridge construction projects from state sales and use
32 taxes; and to allow counties and municipalities to adopt
33 complimentary local sales and use tax exemptions.
34 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
35 Section 1. Sections 40-21-83 and 40-21-103 of the Code
36 of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
37 "§40-21-83
38 There are specifically excluded from the gross receipts
39 or gross sales of a utility, all revenues derived from any of
40 the following:
41 (1) The furnishing of utility services which the State
42 of Alabama is prohibited from taxing under the Constitution or
43 laws of the United States of America or the Constitution of
44 the State of Alabama.
45 (2) The furnishing of utility services which are
46 otherwise taxed under Sections 40-23-1 to 40-23-36, inclusive.
47 (3) Wholesale sales.
48 (4) The furnishing of electricity, natural gas, or
49 domestic water for use or consumption by, in, or for the
50 direct production, generation, processing, storage, delivery,
51 or transmission of electricity, natural gas, or domestic
52 water.
53 (5) The furnishing of electricity to a manufacturer or
54 compounder for use in an electrolytic or electrothermal
55 manufacturing or compounding process.
56 (6) The furnishing of natural gas to a manufacturer or
