87 "§40-21-103
88 The storage, use, or other consumption of utility
89 services in the State of Alabama is hereby specifically
90 excluded from the tax herein levied:
91 (1) Whenever the State of Alabama is prohibited from
92 taxing such storage, use, or consumption under the
93 Constitution or laws of the United States of America or the
94 Constitution of the State of Alabama;
95 (2) Whenever any tax relating to the sale, use,
96 storage, or consumption of said utility services shall be
97 levied under the provisions of Article 2 of Chapter 23 of this
98 title, or under the provisions of Sections 40-23-1 through
99 40-23-36 or the Alabama Transaction Tax Act of 1992 if enacted
100 into law;
101 (3) Whenever the purchase of said utility services
102 shall have been at a wholesale sale;
103 (4) Whenever electricity, natural gas, or domestic
104 water shall have been used or consumed directly in or for the
105 production, generation, processing, storage, delivery, or
106 transmission of electricity, natural gas, or domestic water;
107 (5) Whenever electricity purchased for storage, use, or
108 other consumption is used or consumed by a manufacturer or
109 compounder in an electrolytic or electrothermal manufacturing
110 or compounding process;
111 (6) Whenever natural gas purchased for storage, use, or
112 other consumption is used or consumed by a manufacturer or
