HB531 INTRODUCED
141 governmental entity as defined in Section 40-9-14.1."
142 Section 2. (a)(1) The gross proceeds from the sale of
143 natural gas and liquefied petroleum gas for use in the
144 construction of any public highway, road, or bridge are exempt
145 from state sales and use taxes.
146 (2) This exemption may only be claimed by a contractor
147 licensed by the State Licensing Board for General Contractors,
148 or a subcontractor working under the same contract, for use
149 pursuant to a written contract for and on behalf of a
150 governmental entity as defined in Section 40-9-14.1.
151 (b) Any county or municipality may exempt the products
152 provided in subdivision (a)(1) from county or municipal sales
153 and use taxes under the same conditions provided in
154 subdivision (a)(2) and in accordance with Section 40-23-4.01,
155 Code of Alabama 1975.
156 Section 3. This act shall become effective on September
157 1, 2026.
